data.chText: 标签；标牌
data.enText: a small piece of paper, cloth, plastic, etc. attached to sth to identify it or give information about it

data.chText: 他给自己所有的衬衣都缝上了标有姓名的签条。
data.enText: He put name tags on all his shirts.

data.chText: 礼品签
data.enText: a gift tag (= tied to a present)

data.chText: 警方利用电子跟踪器监视缓刑期间的青年罪犯。
data.enText: The police use electronic tags to monitor the whereabouts of young offenders on probation.

data.chText: 称呼；诨名
data.enText: a name or phrase that is used to describe a person or thing in some way

data.chText: 他们终于准备放弃“新披头士乐队”这一称谓。
data.enText: They are finally ready to drop the tag ‘the new Beatles’.

data.chText: “幸运儿”这个诨名叫了好多年。
data.enText: The ‘lucky’ tag stuck for years.

data.chText: 附加语（为加强语气，如Yes, I do一句中的I do）
data.enText: a word or phrase that is added to a sentence for emphasis, for example I do in Yes, I do

data.chText: 标记；标签；标识符
data.enText: a set of letters or symbols that are put before and after a piece of text or data in order to identify it or show that it is to be treated in a particular way

data.chText: （外国语的）语录，引语，格言，谚语
data.enText: a short quotation or saying in a foreign language

data.chText: 拉丁语格言：“欲要和平，辄需备战。”
data.enText: the Latin tag ‘Si vis pacem, para bellum.’ (= if you want peace, prepare for war)
tig

data.chText: 捉人（儿童游戏）
data.enText: a children's game in which one child chases the others and tries to touch one of them

data.chText: （在公共场所涂鸦者用的）符号，名字
data.enText: a symbol or name used by a graffiti writer and painted in a public place

data.chText: 给…加上标签
data.enText: to fasten a tag onto sth/sb

data.chText: 每只动物都系上了标有号码的小牌，以便辨认。
data.enText: Each animal was tagged with a number for identification.

data.chText: 把…称作；给…起诨名
data.enText: to give sb/sth a name that describes what they are or do

data.chText: 这个国家不愿意再被称为第三世界国家。
data.enText: The country no longer wanted to be tagged as a Third World nation.

data.chText: 加标识符（或标记、标签）于
data.enText: to add a set of letters or symbols to a piece of text or data in order to identify it or show that it is to be treated in a particular way
tag along (behind/with sb)

data.chText: 跟随，尾随（尤指未经同意或邀请）
data.enText: to go somewhere with sb, especially when you have not been asked or invited
tag sth↔on
tag sth onto sth

data.chText: （尤指漫不经心地）给…加上，附加
data.enText: to add sth to the end of sth that already exists, especially in a careless way

data.chText: 信的结尾顺便附了一句抱歉的话。
data.enText: An apology was tagged onto the end of the letter.

data.chText: 以上各词均指标签、标记。
data.enText: These are all words for a piece of paper, fabric or plastic that is attached to sth and gives information about it.
label

data.chText: 指标签、签条、标记：
data.enText: a small piece of paper, fabric or plastic that is attached to sth in order to show what it is or give information about it

data.chText: 洗涤说明在标签上。
data.enText: The washing instructions are on the label.

data.chText: 地址签条
data.enText: address labels

data.chText: 他只愿穿高档名牌服装。
data.enText: He'll only wear clothes with a designer label .
tag

data.chText: （常构成复合词）指标签、标牌：
data.enText: (often used in compounds) a small piece of paper, fabric or plastic that is attached to sth, or that sb wears, in order to give information about it/them

data.chText: 所有与会者必须佩戴身份牌。
data.enText: Everyone at the conference had to wear a name tag.

data.chText: 用label还是tag？
用于服装时，label通常指由织物做成并缝在衣服上的标签，tag通常指挂在衣服上、穿衣服前要剪下的硬纸板标签。name tag指名牌，可贴或系在身上表明佩戴者的身份：
data.enText: Labels in clothes are usually made of fabric and sewn in. Tags on clothes are usually made of cardboard and cut off before you wear the clothes. A name tag can be stuck or tied onto sb to show who they are.

data.chText: 医院里所有婴儿的脚踝上都系有姓名标签。
data.enText: All babies in the hospital have name tags tied round their ankles.
label or tag?

data.chText: price tag指价格标签，较price label常用，既可用作字面意义也可用作比喻意义：
data.enText: Price tag is much more frequent than price label and is used for both literal and figurative meanings.

data.chText: 标价是多少？
data.enText: What does the price tag say?

data.chText: 这名球队主力身价为2千万英镑。
data.enText: There is a £20 million price tag on the team's star player.

data.chText: label亦可指贴在信封上的粘贴标签。
data.enText: A label can also be a sticker that you put on an envelope.
sticker

data.chText: 指粘贴标签、贴纸
data.enText: a sticky label with a picture or message on it, that you stick on to sth
a price label/tag/sticker
a name tag

value.def: A tag is a small piece of card or cloth which is attached to an object or person and has information about that object or person on it.

example.tran: 工作人员都佩戴姓名牌。

value.def: An electronic tag is a device that is firmly attached to someone or something and sets off an alarm if that person or thing moves away or is removed.

example.ex: A hospital is to fit newborn babies with electronic tags to foil kidnappers...
example.tran: 一家医院计划在新生儿身上安置电子追踪器，防止婴儿被拐卖。

example.ex: Sometimes, they've snapped off the security tag and just taken the one shoe.
example.tran: 有时候，他们把防盗标签扯掉，顺走那一只鞋。

value.def: If you tag something, you attach something to it or mark it so that it can be identified later.

example.ex: Professor Orr has developed interesting ways of tagging chemical molecules using existing laboratory lasers...
example.tran: 奥尔教授发明了用现有实验室激光设备给化学分子做记号的种种有趣的办法。

example.ex: The most important trees were tagged to protect them from being damaged by construction machinery.
example.tran: 最珍贵的树木都被贴上了标签，以防被建筑机械毁坏。

value.def: You can refer to a phrase that is used to describe someone or something as a tag .

example.ex: In Britain, jazz is losing its elitist tag and gaining a much broader audience.
example.tran: 在英国，爵士乐不再是精英人物的专利，它正吸引着越来越多的听众。

value.def: If you tag someone in a particular way, you keep describing them using a particular phrase or thinking of them as a particular thing.

example.ex: ...the pundits were still tagging him with that age-old label, 'best of a bad bunch'...
example.tran: 专家们仍用多年前的称呼“最好的坏人”来称呼他。

example.ex: She has always lived in John's house and is still tagged 'Dad's girlfriend' by his children.
example.tran: 她一直住在约翰家里，依然被他的孩子们称作“爸爸的女友”。
